text: Etehomo Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Etehomo Creek is a name most likely derived from the Choctaw language, but its original meaning is obscure. Variant names are "Eatahoma Creek", "Etahoma Creek", "Etchahoma Creek", "Etehoma Creek", and "Etihoma Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Jasper County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Jones County, Mississippi
title: Etehomo Creek
